      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) with documented V&V history; FDA-internal solver configuration controlled under ISO 9001 quality management system.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated solver with published verification benchmarks. FDA OSEL maintains a software quality plan covering version control, regression testing, and analyst qualification records. Achieved level equals required level for Model Risk 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark problems including NAFEMS LE1, LE10, and a contact patch test; results documented in solver qualification report.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical passes NAFEMS linear elastic and contact benchmark suite. Solver qualification report on file confirms code verification for the element types (SOLID186, CONTA174/TARGE170) used in this analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between medium and fine mesh; GCI < 5% for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm global element size at screw-rod interface). GCI values: stiffness 1.4%, yield force 2.1%, force@40mm 3.8%. All below 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization uncertainty contribution to uval."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms converge below 1e-5 for all load steps; energy balance error <0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solution uses full Newton-Raphson with line search. Force residual norm converges to <1e-6 for all 120 load steps across 11 model instances. Energy balance monitored; maximum imbalance 0.04%. No solution divergence events recorded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup, boundary conditions, and loading protocol against ASTM F1717 standard requirements.",
      "rationale": "Model setup peer-reviewed by two independent analysts not involved in original model construction. Boundary conditions, loading fixture geometry, and load application point verified against ASTM F1717-15 Section 8.1. No discrepancies identified. Review checklist retained in project record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening Ti-6Al-4V) justified by coupon-level validation; contact formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface kinematics.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model for Ti-6Al-4V calibrated against ASTM E8 tensile coupon data (N=6, same material lot). Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient μ=0.23 (measured by pin-on-disk tribometry). Geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-deformation regime. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±3.5% of yield force QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus E=114±3 GPa, yield strength σy=880±15 MPa, tangent modulus Et=1.2 GPa derived from lot-specific ASTM E8 coupons. Screw and rod geometry digitized via coordinate measuring machine (CMM) to ±0.01 mm. Input uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo sampling (N=5000 draws) to characterize QoI sensitivity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lot; inter-laboratory comparison with <5% mean difference in QoIs.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested: 6 at FDA OSEL biomechanics laboratory, 5 at DePuy Synthes test facility. All specimens from same production lot (Lot 2021-NC-75). Inter-laboratory mean QoI difference: stiffness 2.1%, yield force 3.4%, force@40mm 4.1%. All below 5% threshold. Specimen traceability records maintained."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing at minimum two load rates or environmental conditions to bound rate and environmental sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single displacement rate (25 mm/min per ASTM F1717) at ambient laboratory conditions. A second load rate condition was planned but not executed due to specimen availability constraints. This factor falls one gradation below the required level. The shortfall is acknowledged; model predictions are therefore constrained to the tested rate condition and should not be extrapolated to dynamic loading scenarios."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs demonstrably matched to experimental specimen properties within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 FEA model instances was parameterized with specimen-specific CMM geometry and lot-specific material properties. Friction coefficient applied uniformly based on tribometry measurement. Input parameter equivalency confirmed by overlay of experimental and model geometry profiles; maximum geometric deviation 0.03 mm."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; all QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 at 95% coverage.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs evaluated: construct stiffness (E/uval=1.31), yield force (E/uval=1.54), force at 40 mm (E/uval=1.78). All below the 1.96 threshold. Comparison plots (force-displacement curves) show good agreement throughout the loading history. No systematic bias detected across the two laboratories."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements for ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relate to clinically relevant failure modes (elastic deformation under physiological load, onset of permanent deformation, and post-yield load-carrying capacity). These QoIs are required in the 510(k) submission and are directly observable in bench testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation specimens, loading configuration, and boundary conditions replicate the COU geometry and loading environment.",
      "rationale": "Validation specimens are production-equivalent non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws assembled per surgical technique guide. ASTM F1717 loading fixture replicates the compression-bending moment arm representative of lumbar spinal loading. The validation activity directly mirrors the COU: same device, same loading mode, same QoIs. Extrapolation distance is minimal."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 due to single-rate testing; this shortfall is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to quasi-static loading at 25 mm/min and the regulatory decision does not require dynamic performance characterization. All three QoIs satisfy the E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use in the 510(k) submission.",
